com.facebook.buck.rules.coercer

Interface ParamInfo

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<ParamInfo>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractParamInfo, ReflectionParamInfo, SkylarkParamInfo

    public interface ParamInfo
extends Comparable<ParamInfo>
    Represents a single field that can be represented in buck build files.

      • traverse

        void traverse(CellPathResolver cellPathResolver,
              ParamInfo.Traversal traversal,
              Object dto)
        Traverse the value of the field on dto that is represented by this instance.

        If this field has a top level Optional type, traversal begins at the Optional value, or not at all if the field is empty.

        Parameters:
        traversal - traversal to apply on the values.
        dto - the object whose field will be traversed.
        See Also:
        TypeCoercer.traverse(CellPathResolver, Object, TypeCoercer.Traversal)

      • getImplicitPreCoercionValue

        @Nullable
Object getImplicitPreCoercionValue()
        Returns:
        The value for this parameter if it is an "implicit" attribute, otherwise null

        This is used for parameters that have a default value and need to be accessed by users' rule implementations, but should not be set directly by users. e.g. underscore prefixed attributes in user defined rules. These values are pre-coercion and may be user provided. If this parameter is not an implicit parameter, this method should return null

      • setCoercedValue

        void setCoercedValue(Object dto,
                     Object value)
        Set the param on dto to value, assuming value has already been coerced.

        This is useful for things like making copies of dtos.

      • getGenericParameterTypes

        Type[] getGenericParameterTypes()
        Get the Types of any generic parameters for the final coerced type.

        e.g. For a parameter that returns a List<String>, this would return an array containing a Type for String

        Returns:
        An array of Types, or an empty array if the type is not generic
